The paper discusses data augmentation methods for time series analysis using deep learning models. The most relevant sub-category is likely cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on improving the performance of deep learning models through data augmentation. Other relevant sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as these fields also heavily rely on deep learning models and may benefit from the data augmentation techniques discussed in the paper.
